    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n#39998 \r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nFor virtual lines, compute the outer fold level and display it by reusing the logic from `fill_foldcolumn`.\r\n\r\nI wanted to avoid adding branches to the condition chain as I think it would have made it harder to maintain. This way the code needed to fix the issue is separate from the old code.\r\n\r\nI also extracted the last three `else if` branches into an `inline` function to not duplicate logic. If that's unwanted (due to it being old vim code) let me know.\r\n\r\nCloses #39998 ",
    "closed_at": null,
